@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: Admin Edit Appointment

actor Admin
participant "Frontend/UI" as UI
participant "Backend/API" as API
participant "Auth Middleware (JWT)" as AUTH
database "Database (Neon)" as DB
participant "Notification Service (Email)" as NOTI

Admin -> UI: Open Appointments Management

Admin -> UI: Click Edit + Modify data
UI -> UI: Validate required fields
UI -> API: PATCH /trl/appointment/{id} (JWT + payload)

API -> AUTH: Verify JWT & role
AUTH --> API: Authorized / Forbidden

alt Forbidden
    API --> UI: 403 Forbidden
    UI --> Admin: Show error
else Authorized
    API -> API: Validate payload
    alt Invalid data
        API --> UI: 400 Validation error
    else Valid
        API -> DB: Check appointment exists
        alt Not found
            API --> UI: 404 Not Found
        else Exists
            API -> DB: Check time conflict
            alt Conflict
                API --> UI: 409 Conflict
            else No conflict
                API -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
                API -> DB: Update appointment
                DB --> API: Update success
                API -> DB: COMMIT
                API -> NOTI: Send update notification (Email)
                NOTI --> API: Sent
                API --> UI: 200 Success
            end
        end
    end
end

UI -> UI: Invalidate query cache
UI --> Admin: Show success toast
UI -> UI: Close edit modal

@enduml